{"key":"processedPost-20959045","value":{"id":20959045,"first":20822448,"last":27653241,"when":1418263630,"utime":"12/11/14 04:07 AM","content":"I met an <i>agaricus blazei</i> grower several years ago who would make up a few hundred substrates in turkey tins covered with foil.&nbsp; He'd place them on the shelves in his insulated grow room and then set up two of those construction heaters(salamanders) just outside the building to blow in heat.&nbsp; He could get the whole building up to around 160F or so where he'd leave it overnight.&nbsp; This also served to kill off mites, gnats, etc., between cropping cycles.<br />RR","title":"Re: EZ Oven Pasteurization 123"}}